    <div class="additional-page-loader">
        <h4 class="mb-2 mt-3 content-title">Loader</h4>
        <p class="mb-2 mt-3 article-content">If you want to add loader in your application then you can add your loader html to your index.html and configure router to show and hide when page is fully loaded.</p>
<pre>
<code class="hljs html">
&lt;!doctype html>
&lt;html lang="en">

&lt;head>
    &lt;title>Your Page&lt;/title>
    &lt;meta content="http://localhost:3000/" name="base_url" />
&lt;/head>

&lt;body>
    &lt;nav class="....">
        ...
    &lt;/nav>

    &lt;div class="container">
        &lt;div class="progress d-none">
            &lt;div class="progress-bar progress-bar-striped progress-bar-animated" role="progressbar" aria-valuenow="100" aria-valuemin="0"
                aria-valuemax="100" style="width: 100%">&lt;/div>
        &lt;/div>
        &lt;div id="app">&lt;/div>
    &lt;/div>

    &lt;footer>
        ...
    &lt;/footer>

    &lt;script src="js/sp-router/sp-router.js">&lt;/script>
    &lt;script src="js/routerConfig.js">&lt;/script>
&lt;/body>

&lt;/html>
</code>
</pre>
        <p class="article-content">Then configure in routerConfig.js</p>
<pre>
<code class="hljs javascript">
var router = new SPRouter({
    content: "#app",
    defaultRoute: "/"
    routes: [
        {
            title: "Products",
            route: "/products",
            template: "views/products/products.html",
            script: "views/products/products.js"
        },
        {
            title: "Product",
            route: "/products/:productId/view",
            template: "views/products/product.html",
            script: "views/products/product.js"
        }
    ],
    loader: {
         selector: ".progress", // your loader class or id selector
    },
});
</code>
</pre>
        <p class="mb-2 mt-3 article-content">This configuration will give show/hide behavior with <b>display:none/block;</b> inline style.</p>
        <p class="article-content">If you want to show/hide with custom class then add <b>showHideClass</b> key to loader configuration.</p>
<pre>
<code class="hljs javascript">
    loader: {
        selector: ".progress",
        showHideClass: "d-none" // your class to show and hide
    },
</code>
</pre>
        <p class="article-content">By default your loader must be <b>hidden (to have your class for hidding)</b> and when router will start loading then will remove your class and when will finish with loading will add your class to hide page loader.</p>
        <p class="article-content">By default when loader is showed up div#app content is hiding. To prevent this behavior provide <b>loadContentHide</b> into loader configuration.</p>
<pre>
<code class="hljs javascript">
    loader: {
        selector: ".progress",
        showHideClass: "d-none",
        loadContentHide: false
    },
</code>
</pre>
